args:
The twin Zethias join powers to strike at the
Other, but the arrival of Zodiark, pactbound
dragon to Aurelius, turns the tables against them.
Zethia is taken anew, leaving the prince to
follow in pursuit.
Return to the world of impurity from\nwhence you came!
They both have the power of the Auspex...\nIt's as if the two of them are channeling\nthe world's blessings together as one!
I will not fall... Not to a pair of children!\nNo... Rraaaaugh!
Has he given up? ...No! This mana—
It's him. It has to be. His mana vanished\nfrom the world for so long I'd wondered\nwhere he'd gone.
But he was pactbound and lurking in the\nshadows this whole time. And now his\npact holder's body has been possessed!
Heh heh heh... Oh, how correct you are.
For when I laid claim to this body, his\npactbound dragon became mine as well.
If you would stack miracle upon miracle,\nI will answer with ever-greater shades of\nwicked darkness!
The Shadowwyrm?! Father held its pact\nthis whole time?!
The last of the Six Greatwyrms...\nI had no idea it remained in the\nroyal family's service.
Tell me, Auspex: Can your fragile form\nwithstand the Shadowwyrm's vast store\nof dark mana?
For his ancient grudge cannot be erased\nby anyone! Now go, Zodiark! Crush them!
I wanted to save {player_name},\nbut even that one wish was...\nbeyond my... Aaah...
Aaaah ha ha ha! Now, my dear Auspex,\nyou will share in her fate!
Heh. Fell unconscious, did she? Well,\nlet that serve as a taste of my power.
I fear it's farewell for now, Prince.\nI await you in the Channeling Chamber.
Come and see what unfolds on its altar,\nif curiosity moves you to do so.\nHeh heh... Aaaah ha ha ha ha!
She was hurting bad... We can't leave her\nlike that!
It never occurred to me that he might have\ntaken hold of Zodiark.
Can we really beat something like that?
Course we can—this story don't end here,\nkid. Now let's get after 'em already!
He's right. Hope is not entirely lost.
Right... Yes, you're right. I can't give up\nwhen {player_name} is hurting.
We'll figure out a way together!
Thank you, Luca. And the rest of you, too.\n
